<subSubSection pageId="157" pageNumber="158" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="157.[151,1438,469,781]" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">
This species does not belong to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="De Prins &amp; De Prins" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[572,741,469,493]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Lithocolletinae">Lithocolletinae</taxonomicName>
according to external morphology. Differently from all 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="De Prins &amp; De Prins" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[151,321,505,529]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Lithocolletinae">Lithocolletinae</taxonomicName>
genera defined by the character indicated in the original description that labial palpi “filiform, drooping ” (
<bibRefCitation author="Stainton" box="[292,516,541,565]" firstAuthor="Stainton" page="264" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" refId="ref199753" refString="Stainton, H. T. (1854) Lepidoptera: Tineina. In: Insecta Britannica. Vol. 3. Lovell Reeve, London, 313 pp, 10 pls." type="book" year="1854">Stainton 1854: 264</bibRefCitation>
), labial palpi in 
<taxonomicName box="[708,821,541,565]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Lithocolletis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurifascia">
<emphasis box="[708,821,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">aurifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are long, porrect; second palpomere with a long tuft beneath, terminal palpomere as long as the second palpomere or slightly longer (
<figureCitation box="[1053,1212,577,601]" captionStart="FIGURES 134–135" captionStartId="209.[151,263,1300,1323]" captionTargetBox="[191,1436,828,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-96@209.[151,1436,828,1279]" captionTargetPageId="209" captionText="FIGURES 134–135. “Lithocolletis” aurifascia Walker 1875, holotype ♂, Saint Helena, leg. Wollaston, in BMNH. 134, adult, habitus. 135, labial palpus long and porrect with a long tuft beneath indicates that aurifascia does not belong to Lithocolletinae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6052212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6052212/files/figure.png" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Figs 134, 135</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="157.[151,1438,469,781]" box="[199,894,613,638]" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis box="[199,252,614,637]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Note</emphasis>
: All five type specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[569,712,613,637]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Lithocolletis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurifascia">
<emphasis box="[569,712,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">L. aurifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lack abdomens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
